OL,3,CCycling athlete and grandad says heart
OL,4,Cstudy 'saved my life'
OL,6,F"I came off the track and looked at my
OL,7,Fheart rate monitor", Brian said, "It
OL,8,Fwas saying 238bpm - and I thought,
OL,9,Fthat's not good. It wasn't going down."
OL,11,FAt the time, Brian was taking part in
OL,12,Fa study by the University of Leeds,
OL,13,Fand funded by the British Heart
OL,14,FFoundation, investigating the heart
OL,15,Fhealth of 106 veteran athletes.
OL,17,FHe had been fitted with an implantable
OL,18,Floop recorder, a small device placed
OL,19,Funder the skin of his chest to record
OL,20,Fhis heart rhythm that was recording
OL,21,Fevery one of his heartbeats.
OL,1,W~s1{$~k4{$k7                    G3/8
